{sort|020|[[Interlachen Country Club]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|035|1}}\n|1930\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|063|MN}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |{{sort|047|[[The Minikahda Club]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|042|1}}\n|1916\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|064|MN}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|058|[[Minnesota|Total Minnesota]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|060|4}}\n|style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|065|WNC}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |{{sort|004|[[Bellerive Country Club]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|027|1}}\n|1965\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|066|MO}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |{{sort|045|[[St. Louis Country Club]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|030|1}}\n|1947\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|067|MO}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|059|[[Missouri|Total Missouri]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|065|2}}\n|style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|068|WNC}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |{{sort|045|[[Erin Hills]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|030|1}}\n|2017\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|067|WI}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|059|[[Wisconsin|Total Wisconsin]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|065|1}}\n|style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|068|WNC}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Pink\"|{{sort|075|[[West North Central States|Total West North Central]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Pink\"|{{sort|073|7}}\n|style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Pink\"|\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Pink\"|{{sort|069|Midwest}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"font-weight:bold;background:paleturquoise\"|{{sort|077|[[Midwestern United States|Total Midwest]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:paleturquoise\"|{{sort|078|33}}\n|style=\"font-weight:bold;background:paleturquoise\"|\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:paleturquoise\"|{{sort|070|USA}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |{{sort|009|[[Cherry Hills Country Club]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|016|3}}\n|1978, 1960, 1938\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|071|CO}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|052|[[Colorado|Total Colorado]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|061|3}}\n|style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|072|Mtn}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Pink\"|{{sort|071|[[Mountain States|Total Mountain]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Pink\"|{{sort|075|3}}\n|style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Pink\"|\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Pink\"|{{sort|073|West}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |{{sort|034|[[Olympic Club]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|005|5}}\n|2012,1998,1987,1966,<br/>1955\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|074|CA}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |{{sort|036|[[Pebble Beach Golf Links]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|006|6}}\n|2019,2010,2000,1992,1982,<br/>1972\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|075|CA}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |{{sort|048|[[Torrey Pines Golf Course]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|024|1}}\n|2008\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|076|CA}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |{{sort|040|[[Riviera Country Club]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|029|1}}\n|1948\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|077|CA}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|051|[[California|Total California]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|054|13}}\n|style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|078|Pac}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |{{sort|007a|[[Chambers Bay]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|023a|1}}\n|2015\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|{{sort|078a|WA}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|067a|[[Washington (state)|Total Washington]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|067a|1}}\n|style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Khaki\"|{{sort|078b|Pac}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Pink\"|{{sort|073|[[Pacific States|Total Pacific]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Pink\"|{{sort|070|14}}\n|style=\"font-weight:bold;background:Pink\"|\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:Pink\"|{{sort|079|West}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"font-weight:bold;background:paleturquoise\"|{{sort|080|[[Western United States|Total West]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:paleturquoise\"|{{sort|079|17}}\n|style=\"font-weight:bold;background:paleturquoise\"|\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:paleturquoise\"|{{sort|080|USA}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"font-weight:bold;background:lightgreen\"|{{sort|081|[[United States|Total U.S. Opens]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:lightgreen\"|{{sort|081|119}}\n|style=\"font-weight:bold;background:lightgreen\"|\n|style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold;background:lightgreen\"|{{sort|081| }}\n|-\n|}\n\nThe eighteenth state to host the tournament was [[Washington (state)|Washington]] in 2015, followed by [[Wisconsin]] in 2017.\n\n==Records==\n* Oldest champion: [[Hale Irwin]] in 1990 at {{Age in years and days|1945|6|3|1990|6|18}}.\n* Youngest champion: [[John McDermott (golfer)|John McDermott]] in 1911 at 19 years, 315 days.\n* Oldest player to make the cut: [[Sam Snead]] in 1973 at 61 years old. He tied for 29th place.\n* Most victories: 4 by Willie Anderson 1901, 1903\u20131905; Bobby Jones 1923, 1926, 1929\u201330; Ben Hogan 1948, 1950\u201351, 1953; Jack Nicklaus 1962, 1967, 1972, 1980. NOTE: Hogan also won the 1942 Hale America National Open which was held jointly by the USGA, PGA and Chicago GA for the benefit of the Navy Relief Society and the USO.\n* Most consecutive victories: 3 by [[Willie Anderson (golfer)|Willie Anderson]] 1903\u20131905.\n* Most consecutive victorious attempts: 3 by Ben Hogan 1948, 1950\u201351\n* Most consecutive attempts in top 2: 5 by Bobby Jones 1922\u20131926\n* Most consecutive attempts in top 5: 6 by Willie Anderson 1901\u20131906\n* Most consecutive attempts in top 10: 16 by Ben Hogan 1940\u20131956 (next highest streak 7)\n* Most runner-up finishes: [[Phil Mickelson]] \u2013 6 (1999, 2002, 2004, 2006, 2009, 2013)\n* Most consecutive Opens started: 44 by [[Jack Nicklaus]] from 1957 to 2000.\n* Largest margin of victory: 15 strokes by [[Tiger Woods]], 2000. This is the all-time record for all majors.\n* Lowest score for 36 holes: 130 \u2013 [[Martin Kaymer]] (65\u201365), rounds 1\u20132, 2014.\n* Lowest score for 54 holes: 199 \u2013 [[Rory McIlroy]] (65\u201366\u201368), rounds 1\u20133, 2011; [[Louis Oosthuizen]] (66-66-67), rounds 2-4, 2015.\n* Lowest score for 72 holes: 268 \u2013 [[Rory McIlroy]] (65\u201366\u201368\u201369), rounds 1\u20134, 2011.\n* Most strokes under par for 72 holes: 16-under (268) by [[Rory McIlroy]], 2011; 16-under (272) by [[Brooks Koepka]], 2017.\n* Most strokes under par at any point in the tournament: 17 by [[Rory McIlroy]], final round, 2011.<ref name=McIlroy>{{cite news |url=http://sports.espn.go.com/golf/usopen11/news/story?id=6678101 |title=Rory McIlroy runs away with Open title |work=ESPN |date=June 20, 2011 |accessdate=June 20, 2011}}</ref>\n* Lowest score for 18 holes: 63 \u2013 [[Johnny Miller]], 4th round, 1973; [[Jack Nicklaus]], 1st, 1980; [[Tom Weiskopf]], 1st, 1980; [[Vijay Singh]], 2nd, 2003; [[Justin Thomas (golfer)|Justin Thomas]], 3rd, 2017; [[Tommy Fleetwood]], 4th, 2018.\n* Lowest score for 18 holes in relation to par: \u22129 [[Justin Thomas (golfer)|Justin Thomas]], 3rd round, 2017.\n* All four rounds under par (golfers who did not win the tournament in ''italics''):<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2011/jun/19/us-open-day-four-live |title=US Open 2011 \u2013 day four as it happened |newspaper=The Guardian |first=Scott |last=Murray |date=June 19, 2011 |accessdate=June 12, 2013}}</ref>\n** [[Lee Trevino]], [[1968 U.S. Open (golf)|1968]] (69\u201368\u201369\u201369, par 70)\n** [[Tony Jacklin]], [[1970 U.S. Open (golf)|1970]] (71\u201370\u201370\u201370, par 72)\n** [[Lee Janzen]], [[1993 U.S. Open (golf)|1993]] (67\u201367\u201369\u201369, par 70)\n** ''[[Curtis Strange]]'', [[1994 U.S. Open (golf)|1994]] (70\u201370\u201370\u201370, par 71)\n** [[Rory McIlroy]] (65\u201366\u201368\u201369, par 71) and ''[[Robert Garrigus]]'' (70\u201370\u201368\u201370), [[2011 U.S. Open (golf)|2011]]\n** [[Brooks Koepka]] (67\u201370\u201368\u201367, par 72), ''[[Charley Hoffman]]'' (70\u201370\u201368\u201371), and ''[[Brandt Snedeker]]'' (70\u201369\u201370\u201371), [[2017 U.S. Open (golf)|2017]]\n* All four rounds under 70: Trevino, 1968; Janzen, 1993; McIlroy, 2011.<ref name=McIlroy/>\n* Most frequent venues:\n** 9 Opens: [[Oakmont Country Club]] \u2013 1927, 1935, 1953, 1962, 1973, 1983, 1994, 2007, 2016\n** 7 Opens: [[Baltusrol Golf Club]] \u2013 1903, 1915, 1936, 1954, 1967, 1980, 1993\n** 6 Opens: \n***[[Oakland Hills Country Club]] \u2013 1924, 1937, 1951, 1961, 1985, 1996\n*** [[Pebble Beach Golf Links]] \u2013 1972, 1982, 1992, 2000, 2010, 2019\n** 5 Opens: \n***[[Winged Foot Golf Club]] \u2013 1929, 1959, 1974, 1984, 2006\n*** [[Olympic Club]] \u2013 1955, 1966, 1987, 1998, 2012\n*** [[Merion Golf Club]] \u2013 1934, 1950, 1971, 1981, 2013\n*** [[Shinnecock Hills Golf Club]] \u2013 1896, 1986, 1995, 2004, 2018\n** 4 Opens: \n***[[Myopia Hunt Club]] \u2013 1898, 1901, 1905, 1908\n*** [[Inverness Club]] \u2013 1920, 1931, 1957, 1979\n\nThere is an extensive records section on the official U.S. Open website.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.usopen.com/history-landing/scoring-and-stats/records.html#!&y=2017 |title=U.S. Open History \u2013 Records |publisher=USGA |access-date=June 17, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Broadcasting==\n{{main|List of U.S. Open (golf) broadcasters}}\n\nAs of 2015, [[Fox Sports (United States)|Fox Sports]] is the official broadcaster of the U.S. Open,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.classictvsports.com/2013/06/history-of-us-open-golf-tv-coverage.html |title=History of US Open golf TV coverage (1954-present) |last=Haggar |first=Jeff |date=June 10, 2013 |website=Classic TV Sports}}</ref> as the result of a 12-year deal with the USGA for exclusive rights to its tournaments through 2026. Coverage will be telecast by [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] (over-the-air) and [[Fox Sports 1|FS1]] (cable).<ref name=\"bc-foxusopen\">{{cite web |url=http://www.broadcastingcable.com/article/494969-Fox_Sports_Reaches_Rights_Deal_for_Golf_s_U_S_Open.php |title=Fox Sports Reaches Rights Deal for Golf's U.S. Open |last=Baysinger |first=Tim |date=August 7, 2013 |website=Broadcasting & Cable |accessdate=August 7, 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe 2019 edition of the U.S. Open featured a total of 38 hours of coverage in the United States, with 20 hours being on Thursday and Friday, and 18 hours being on Saturday and Sunday; the Fox Sports 1 cable network carried a total of 14 hours of coverage on Thursday and Friday. The Fox broadcast network had a total of 24 hours of coverage Thursday through Sunday, with 6 hours Thursday and Friday, and 18 hours Saturday and Sunday. The overall 38\u2013hour total is up 1 hour from last year's total of 37 hours, due to the Fox broadcast network's coverage having 24 hours this year, compared to the 23.5 hours it had last year, and the Fox Sports 1 cable network's 14 hours this year, compared to the 13.5 hours it had last year.\n\nCoverage was previously televised by [[Golf Channel on NBC|NBC]] and [[Golf on ESPN|ESPN]] through [[2014 U.S. Open (golf)|2014]]. NBC's most recent period as rightsholder began in [[1995 U.S. Open (golf)|1995]]; [[PGA Tour on ABC|ABC]] held the broadcast rights from [[1966 U.S. Open (golf)|1966]] through [[1994 U.S. Open (golf)|1994]].<ref name=sylat>{{cite magazine |url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/vault/article/magazine/MAG1005339/index.htm |magazine=Sports Illustrated |last=Rosaforte |first=Tim |title=See Ya Later |date=June 27, 1994 |page=49 |accessdate=June 12, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Australia]], from 2015 [[Fox Sports (Australia)|Fox Sports Australia]] is the exclusive broadcaster of the U.S. open until 2018.<ref name=\"foxgolf15\">{{cite web |website=[[TV Tonight]] |first=David |last=Knox |url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2015/04/fox-sports-tees-off-with-more-golf.html |title=Fox Sports tees off with more Golf |date=April 9, 2015 |accessdate=April 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Future sites==\n{| class=wikitable\n!Year\n!Edition\n!Course\n!Location\n!Dates\n!Times hosted\n|-\n| align=center| [[2020 U.S. Open (golf)|2020]] || align=center| 120th || [[Winged Foot Golf Club]], West Course || [[Mamaroneck, New York]] || June 18\u201321 || [[1929 U.S. Open (golf)|1929]], [[1959 U.S. Open (golf)|1959]], [[1974 U.S. Open (golf)|1974]], [[1984 U.S. Open (golf)|1984]], [[2006 U.S. Open (golf)|2006]]\n|-\n| align=center| 2021 || align=center| 121st || [[Torrey Pines Golf Course]], South Course || [[La Jolla|La Jolla, California]] || June 17\u201320 || [[2008 U.S. Open (golf)|2008]]\n|-\n| align=center| 2022 || align=center| 122nd || [[The Country Club]] || [[Brookline, Massachusetts]] || June 16\u201319 || [[1913 U.S. Open (golf)|1913]], [[1963 U.S. Open (golf)|1963]], [[1988 U.S. Open (golf)|1988]]\n|-\n| align=cente