ecember 2004}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Woodward|first1=Ralph Lee|title=Rafael Carrera and the Emergence of the Republic of Guatemala, 1821\u20131871|location=Athens, GA|publisher=University of Georgia Press|year=1993|url=http://muse.jhu.edu/books/9780820343600|isbn=978-0-8203-1448-8|ref=harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{See also|Bibliography of Guatemala}}\n{{refbegin|30em}}\n* {{cite news|newspaper= [[Diario de Centro Am\u00e9rica]] |title = Interview from Enrique G\u00f3mez Carrillo with His Excellency, President Manuel Estrada Cabrera |year = 1898|location=Guatemala|last=G\u00f3mez Carrillo|first=Enrique|author-link=Enrique G\u00f3mez Carrillo|language=Spanish}}\n* {{cite journal|url=https://www.academia.edu/3681333|title=The CIA and Jacobo Arbenz: The story of a disinformation campaign|last=Garcia Ferreira|first=Roberto|journal=Journal of Third World Studies|year=2008|volume=XXV|issue=2|pages=59|location=United States}}\n* {{cite book|last=Koeppel|first=Dan|title=Banana: The Fate of the Fruit That Changed the World|url=https://archive.org/details/bananafateoffrui00koep|url-access=registration|year=2008|publisher=Hudson Street Press|location=New York|page=[https://archive.org/details/bananafateoffrui00koep/page/153 153]|isbn=9781101213919}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Krehm|first=William|title=Democracies and Tyrannies of the Caribbean in the 1940s|publisher=COMER Publications|year=1999|isbn=978-1-896266-81-7|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dAUd1NHWGhIC}}\n* {{cite book|last=Marroqu\u00edn Rojas|first=Clemente|title=Francisco Moraz\u00e1n y Rafael Carrera|publisher=Piedrasanta|location=Guatemala|year=1971|language=Spanish}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Mart\u00ednez Pel\u00e1ez|first=Severo|title=Racismo y An\u00e1lisis Hist\u00f3rico de la Definici\u00f3n del Indio Guatemalteco|publisher=Universitaria|location=Guatemala|year=1988|language=Spanish}}\n* {{cite book|last=Mart\u00ednez Pel\u00e1ez|first=Severo|title=La patria del criollo; ensayo de interpretaci\u0