nish}}\n* {{cite book|first=Terry|last=Rugeley|title=Yucatan's Maya Peasantry and the Origins of the Caste War|location=San Antonio, TX|publisher=University of Texas|year=1996|isbn=978-0-292-77078-2}}\n* {{cite book|first=Terry|last=Rugeley|title=Maya Wars: Ethnographic Accounts from Nineteenth Century Yucatan|publisher=University of Oklahoma Press|location=Norman|year=2001|isbn=978-0-8061-3355-3|url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Maya_Wars.html?id=dildxZvRwxQC}}\n* {{Cite book|title=Guatemala, la historia silenciada (1944\u20131989)|volume=Tomo 1: Revoluci\u00f3n y Liberaci\u00f3n|publisher=Fondo Nacional para la Cultura Econ\u00f3mica|location=Guatemala|year=2007|last=Sabino|first=Carlos|language=Spanish}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Stephens|first1=John Lloyd|last2=Catherwood|first2=Frederick|url=https://archive.org/details/incidentstravel00cathgoog|title=Incidents of travel in Central America, Chiapas, and Yucatan|publisher=Arthur Hall, Virtue and Co.|year=1854|location=London, England}}\n* {{Cite book|last1=Striffler|first1=Steve|last2=Moberg|first2=Mark|title=Banana wars: power, production, and history in the Americas|publisher=Duke University Press|year=2003|isbn=978-0-8223-3196-4|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/bananawars01unse}}\n* {{cite book|first=Arturo|last=Taracena|title=Invenci\u00f3n criolla, sue\u00f1o ladino, pesadilla indigena, Los Altos de Guatemala: de regi\u00f3n a Estado, 1740\u20131871|location=Guatemala|publisher=Biblioteca b\u00e1sica de historia de Guatemala|year=2011|edition=3rd|isbn=978-9929-587-42-7|url=http://www.afehc-historia-centroamericana.org/index.php?action=fi_aff&id=244|language=Spanish|access-date=10 February 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160109073146/http://www.afehc-historia-centroamericana.org/index.php?action=fi_aff&id=244|archive-date=9 January 2016|url-status=dead}}\n* {{cite book |title=Politics of Latin America: The Power Game |editor=Harry E. Vanden |editor2=Gary Prevost |publisher=Oxford University Press |year=2002 |isbn=0-19-512317-4 |chapter=Chapter Ten: Guatemala}}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Sister project links|voy=Guatemala}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20130117025729/http://uzonreport.com/?page_id=124 Guatemala After the War 1996\u20132000, Photographs by Jorge Uzon]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20180309063237/http://latitudylongitud.com/ Guatemala Map Search with Longitude and Latitude]\n* [http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/701217/Guatemala Guatemala&nbsp;\u2013 Country Article] Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090814100556/http://www.guatemala.gob.gt/ Government of Guatemala] {{in lang|es}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20081210073759/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/world-leaders-1/world-leaders-g/guatemala.html Chief of State and Cabinet Members]\n* {{CIA World Factbook link|gt|Guatemala}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080607084913/http://ucblibraries.colorado.edu/govpubs/for/guatemala.htm Guatemala] at ''UCB Libraries GovPubs''.\n* {{curlie|Regional/Central_America/Guatemala}}\n* [http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/country_profiles/1215758.stm Guatemala profile] from the [[BBC News]].\n* {{Wikiatlas|Guatemala}}\n* [http://www.ifs.du.edu/ifs/frm_CountryProfile.aspx?Country=GT Key Development Forecasts for Guatemala] from [[International Futures]].\n* [http://www.gwu.edu/~nsarchiv/guatemala/ The National Security Archive: Guatemala Project]\n* [http://www.inguat.gob.gt/ Guatemala Tourism Commission]\n* [http://wits.worldbank.org/CountryProfile/Country/GTM/Year/2012/Summary World Bank Summary Trade Statistics Guatemala]\n\n{{Geographic location\n |Centre = {{flag|Guatemala}}\n |N  = {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Yucat\u00e1n Peninsula]]\n |NE = {{flag|Belize}}\n |E  = ''[[Caribbean Sea]]''<br />{{flag|Honduras}}\n |SE = {{flag|El Salvador}}\n |S  = ''[[Pacific Ocean]]''\n |SW = ''[[Pacific Ocean]]''\n |W  = {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Chiapas]]\n |NW = {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Tabasco]]\n}}\n\n{{Guatemala topics}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Geographic locale\n|list =\n{{Departments of Guatemala}}\n{{Central America topic}}\n{{Countries of North America}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Guatemala| ]]<!--please leave the empty space as standard-->\n[[Category:Countries in Central America]]\n[[Category:Former Spanish colonies]]\n[[Category:Member states of the United Nations]]\n[[Category:Republics]]\n[[Category:Spanish-speaking countries and territories]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1821]]\n[[Category:1821 establishments in North America]]\n[[Category:Countries in North America]]\n[[Category:Northern Triangle of Central America]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the country in Central America}}\n{{pp-pc1|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Country in Central America}}\n{{more citations needed|date=June 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Coord|15|30|N|90|15|W|display=title}}\n{{Infobox country\n| conventional_long_name = Republic of Guatemala\n| common_name = Guatemala\n| native_name = {{native name|es|Rep\u00fablica de Guatemala}}\n| image_flag = Flag of Guatemala.svg\n| image_coat = Coat of arms of Guatemala.svg\n| national_motto = {{unbulleted list\n  |\"''Libre Crezca Fecundo''\"{{sfn|Banco de Guatemala|1996|p=}}<small> (Spanish)<br />({{Lang-en|\"Grow Free and Fertile\"}})</small>\n}}\n| national_anthem = <br />''[[National anthem of Guatemala|Himno Nacional de Guatemala]]''<br />({{Lang-en|\"National Anthem of Guatemala\"}})<br /><center>[[File:Gutemala's national anthem, performed by the U.S. Navy Band.ogg]]</center>\n| other_symbol = ''[[La Granadera]]''<br />({{Lang-en|\"The Song of the Grenadier\"}})<br />{{center|[[File:La Granadera.ogg]]}}\n| other_symbol_type = March:\n| image_map = Guatemala (orthographic projection).svg\n| map_caption = {{map caption |location_color=dark green\n| region=the [[Western Hemisphere]] |region_color=grey}}\n| image_map2 = Guatemala - Location Map (2013) - GTM - UNOCHA.svg\n| capi